<TEXT>
A newspaper reported Saturday that more than 
80000 files have been stolen from a Nazi documentation center in 
Berlin 
The Berliner Morgenpost tabloid claimed many of the missing 
files from the Berlin Document Center were sold to collectors 
around the world and some were used to blackmail former Nazis 
The report which is to be published in the newspapers Sunday 
edition quoted unnamed West German investigators and could not 
immediately be confirmed 
The newspaper telexed a copy of its report to other news media 
in advance 
Many of the documents contained secret information about 
leading figures in the Third Reich the newspaper said 
The newspaper said West German investigators believe the 
documents were sold for incredible sums 
</TEXT>
